---
title: "Connect apple calendar with calcom"
---

To connect apple calendar with cal.com, please complete the following steps:

1. Go to [https://cal.com/apps/categories/calendar](https://cal.com/apps/categories/calendar) and click on Details under the Apple Calendar card. {% img src="/docs/images/i1600x900-_e9Av_BR4yzA_qecpmk.png" /%}

2. Click on the Install button or, if you already have an Apple Calendar connection, click on Install another button. {% img src="/docs/images/i1600x900-qJHsVoNdhG4E_cbx1zr.png" /%}

3. In the Apple Calendar connection setup page, click on the link and sign in to your appleID. {% img src="/docs/images/i1600x900-J9PsGW5M9u6y_ovzalk.png" /%}

4. Once signed in and on the [https://appleid.apple.com/account/manage](https://appleid.apple.com/account/manage) page, click on App-specific passwords. {% img src="/docs/images/i1600x900-8KLW-ewrcf-6_qkibok.png" /%}

5. Now, click on the plus sign to add a new App-specific password to your account. {% img src="/docs/images/i1600x900-ibCXjqOd05ZH_qycqgt.png" /%}

6. Next, provide a name for your new App-specific password{% img src="/docs/images/i1600x900-GsO3fgUZ0Qbl_aguqa8.png" /%}

7. You should now have a new app-specific password showing on the screen. Simply copy this password{% img src="/docs/images/i1600x900--1flu1Jm22OG_agrtll.png" /%}

8. Now enter your apple ID and the newly generated app-specific password (you copied this in the previous step) in the Cal.com's [Apple Calendar Setup](https://cal.com/apps/apple-calendar/setup) page{% img src="/docs/images/i1600x900-I68apHEG1aUi_r85ufb.png" /%}

9. Finally, click on save. You should now be redirected to [https://cal.com/apps/installed/calendar](https://cal.com/apps/installed/calendar) page showing your recently added Apple Calendar{% img src="/docs/images/i1600x900-pVQwZTGaR5hD_gydirn.png" /%}

That's it. Your Apple Calendar is now connected to your [Cal.com](https://cal.com) account